BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:3XP2qcUH2YlUAaDcUwXnz
SUMMARY:Journaling the Garden
DTSTAMP:20260307T070423Z
DTSTART:20260307T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:Nature journaling at the Bellevue Botanical Garden is a wonderf
	ul way to connect with the environment through curiosity and observation o
	f the natural world. This free adult program will help guide your practice
	 whether you are just starting out or are an experienced journaler. In thi
	s warm and welcoming environment\, you will be encouraged to experiment an
	d find your voice. In each session we will gather for introductions and br
	ief guidance\, and then head out into Garden to journal and come back toge
	ther to share experiences.   \n\nPlease bring a dedicated journal and some
	thing to write with. We will meet at 9am the first Saturday of January-Nov
	ember 2026. Registration is recommended but not required. REGISTER NOW.  \
	n\nThis free adult program is facilitated by Anne Dziok\, Adult Education 
	Program Manager. Anne is a practicing multi-media artist who shows her wor
	k regionally.    \n\nEmail us  with questions.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity
	.com/events/#/details/journaling-the-garden/17658183/2026-03-07T00
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/journaling-the-garden/176
	58183/2026-03-07T00
LOCATION:Sharp Cabin\, 12001 Main St\, Bellevue\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:1-Ra_uX4n9CIRj05qak2f
SUMMARY:Myra Albert WIGGINS Celebrating a Pacific Northwest woman pioneer i
	n early American photography
DTSTAMP:20260307T070423Z
DTSTART:20260307T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Description   Exhibition and sale of rare vintage photographs b
	y women American pioneer photographer and painter Myra Albert Wiggins \\(1
	869-1956\\) All works presented are original vintage prints\, executed in 
	platinum and gelatin silver\, and printed by the artist herself between 18
	95 and 1910.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/myra-albert-
	wiggins-celebrating-a-pacific-northwest-woman-pioneer-in-early-american-ph
	otography/18243908/2026-03-07T00
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/myra-albert-wiggins-celeb
	rating-a-pacific-northwest-woman-pioneer-in-early-american-photography/182
	43908/2026-03-07T00
LOCATION:Loveless Building\, Seattle\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:Z3fljcX9O-IPoSHrOjzDf
SUMMARY:TADAIMA: I'm Home
DTSTAMP:20260307T070423Z
DTSTART:20260307T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:After more than 80 years\, a treasured collection returns “home
	” to Seattle’s Japanese American community. In 1942 dozens of traditional 
	Boys’ and Girls’ Day dolls were entrusted to Bailey Gatzert Elementary Sch
	ool by Japanese American families facing forced incarceration. Most were n
	ever reclaimed after the war. Artist Miya Sukune uses recent research in M
	OHAI’s collection\, as well as interviews with Japanese American survivors
	 and their descendants\, to create an installation called “Tadaima\,” mean
	ing “I’m home.”\n\nTADAIMA: “I’m Home!” Bringing Seattle’s Girls’ and Boys
	’ Day Dolls Home reconnects the dolls with their traditional role of prote
	cting and blessing children. It invites visitors to celebrate the resilien
	ce\, memory\, and enduring traditions of the Japanese American Community.\
	n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/tadaima-i-m-home/18096356
	/2026-03-07T00
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/tadaima-i-m-home/18096356
	/2026-03-07T00
LOCATION:Museum of History and Industry\, 860 Terry Ave N\, Seattle\, Seatt
	le\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT7H
END:VEVENT
